## Deploy Commands
Use `deploy/update.sh` for mcp-stack services:
```bash
sudo bash /home/cdapi/mcp-stack/deploy/update.sh all
sudo bash /home/cdapi/mcp-stack/deploy/update.sh centerdevice
sudo bash /home/cdapi/mcp-stack/deploy/update.sh bidrento
```

For other services, use the single-line pattern:
```bash
su - [user] -c "cd ~/[repo] && git pull && npm run build" && systemctl restart [service]
```

NEVER use multi-line blocks for deploy commands.

## Nginx
- Main server block: `deploy/nginx/box.makkib.com.conf`
- Per-service includes: `deploy/nginx/mcp.d/*.conf`
- Adding a new MCP = one `.conf` file in `mcp.d/` + `nginx -t && systemctl reload nginx`

## Adding a New MCP Service
1. Create `packages/{service}/` with `client.ts`, `tools.ts`, `index.ts`
2. Add `package.json` depending on `@mcp-stack/core`
3. Add workspace to root `package.json`
4. Create `deploy/nginx/mcp.d/{service}.conf`
5. Create `deploy/systemd/mcp-{service}.service`
6. On VPS: create system user, clone repo, install unit, reload nginx
7. Connect in Claude.ai settings

## Firewall Rules
```bash
iptables -A INPUT -p tcp --dport [PORT] -j ACCEPT
iptables-save > /etc/iptables/rules.v4
```

## Environment & Config
- `.env` files for runtime config, `.env.example` committed
- Secrets NEVER committed — managed on VPS directly
- See `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for all env vars per service
